/ Base
%section#helpers.element-group
  %h1.section-title Base
  %p.intro
    :markdown
      Survival Kit default variables
  %div.example
    %h3.step
      %a.permalink{:href => "#reset"}
        :preserve
          Pick a reset or normalization
    #reset.extendable-source
      .comment
        :markdown
          - accepted values: 'meyer' (default), 'normalize', 'none'
          - choose to reset header sizes (applies to 'normalize' only)
          - use [Formalize](http://formalize.me/)
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          // $init-headers: true;
          $init-type: normalize;
          $formalize: true;
  %div.example
    %h3.step
      %a.permalink{:href => "#pixel-normalize"}
        :preserve
          Pixel-normalize
    #pixel-normalize.extendable-source
      .comment
        :markdown
          - [A List Apart](http://www.alistapart.com/articles/a-pixel-identity-crisis/)
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          $pixel-normalize: true;
  %div.example
    %h3.step
      %a.permalink{:href => "#font-size-leading"}
        :preserve
          - Font size and line-height
    #font-size-leading.extendable-source
      / .comment
      /   :markdown
      /     - [A List Apart](http://www.alistapart.com/articles/a-pixel-identity-crisis/)
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          $base-font-size: 16px;
          $base-line-height: $base-font-size * 1.5;
  %div.example
    %h3.step
      %a.permalink{:href => "#modular-scale"}
        :preserve
          Modular Scale
    #modular-scale.extendable-source
      .comment
        :markdown
          - values used to determine modular scale values
          - [link](http://modularscale.com/)
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          $ratio: golden_ratio() major_third();
          $base-size: $base-font-size;
  %div.example
    %h3.step
      %a.permalink{:href => "#dimensions"}
        :preserve
          Dimensions
    #dimensions.extendable-source
      .comment
        :markdown
          - basic values, independant of any css framework
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          $kit-baseline: $base-line-height;
          $kit-baseline-half: $kit-baseline * 0.5;
          $kit-baseline-neg: $kit-baseline * -1;
          $kit-gutter: ms(2);
          $kit-gutter-half: $kit-gutter * 0.5;
          $kit-gutter-neg: $kit-gutter * -1;
  %div.example
    %h3.step
      %a.permalink{:href => "#baseline"}
        :preserve
          use the Compass baseline system
    #baseline.extendable-source
      / .comment
      /   :markdown
      /     - basic values, independant of any css framework
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          $establish-baseline: true;
  %div.example
    %h3.step
      %a.permalink{:href => "#headers"}
        :preserve
          Headers
    #headers.extendable-source
      .comment
        :markdown
          - create a list of header sizes, H1 - H6
          - Use Compass&rsquo;s adjust-font-size-to function
          - fancy apersands - for .amp within headers
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          $header-sizes: ms(6) ms(5) ms(4) ms(3) ms(2) ms(1);
          $adjust-font-size-to: true;
          $header-ampersands: false;
  %div.example
    %h3.step
      %a.permalink{:href => "#links"}
        :preserve
          Links
    #links.extendable-source
      .comment
        :markdown
          - replace normal link underlines with bottom borders
          - animate link hovers. use a 'time' value, like '0.5s'
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          $border-links: false;
          $link-transitions: false;
  %div.example
    %h3.step
      %a.permalink{:href => "#forms"}
        :preserve
          Forms
    #forms.extendable-source
      / .comment
      /   :markdown
      /     - replace normal link underlines with bottom borders
      /     - animate link hovers. use a 'time' value, like '0.5s'
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          $kit-form-defaults: false;
  %div.example
    %h3.step
      %a.permalink{:href => "#grid-variables"}
        :preserve
          Grid Variables
    #grid-variables.extendable-source
      .comment
        :markdown
          - note: set grid system-specific variables in the grid section (06)
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          $show-grid: false;
          $show-baseline: false;
  %div.example
    %h3.step
      %a.permalink{:href => "#animate"}
        :preserve
          Animate all the things
    #animate.extendable-source
      .comment
        :markdown
          - useful for previewing css changes.
          - do something more targeted in production, ok?
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          $animate-all-the-things: false;
